## Design Decisions

This section records project-level design decisions and rationale. For current implementation details, including deployed resource definitions, host pool settings, module structure, and pipeline behavior, review the Bicep and Azure DevOps pipeline files in the repository.

* AVD session hosts will be Active Directory Domain Services joined to the `TV.local` domain.
* FSLogix will be used for user profile containers.
* Profiles will be stored in Azure Files storage.
* Infrastructure will be deployed using Bicep.
* Azure DevOps pipelines will be used for deployment automation.
* Azure Verified Modules should be used where practical.
* The PoC is disposable and should not be treated as the final production deployment.
* If production proceeds, a new environment will be deployed using the lessons and IaC from this PoC.
* The deployment target is the True Value Azure tenant.
* The workload should live in the Corp Landing Zone.
* Use Operations pooled, Development pooled, and Development personal host pools, and possibly in the future add an Operations personal host pool.

  * This validates the major user personas while preserving an exception path for users who cannot work in pooled desktops.
* Deploy AVD in the True Value tenant.
* Use a shared Azure network hub subscription because the Azure network hub can provide centralized connectivity into the True Value network for AVD and future Azure resources.

  * The network hub will live in `connectivity-sub-prod`.
  * The AVD spoke network will peer to the hub.
  * Traffic from AVD session hosts to True Value resources will route through the hub and then through the True Value GCP network hub.
* Use one modular repository with separate deployment entry points because it provides clear deployment boundaries without creating premature repository sprawl.
* Use controlled idle, disconnect, logoff, and scaling behavior because the PoC must test AVD as a controlled and cost-aware operating model.
* Deploy lightweight PoC monitoring with a dedicated Log Analytics workspace because the PoC needs enough telemetry to support troubleshooting and cost modeling without overbuilding production monitoring.
* Plan a separate personal desktop lifecycle workflow because personal desktops have a different lifecycle than core AVD infrastructure.

